<subSubSection id="0E3E558A5F3B7540F6BA99D12F1F9379" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="51BF2D85FF42EBBF075100E6D273D3D8" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="55DB3E11EA3F02CAB975E7140E10F048" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">
One of the key characters discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="570734D5D8471899875BC354A74C9B68" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" author="Kvist, L" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 83" refId="B4" refString="Kvist, L, Skog, LE, 1992. Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 79 (79): 1 - 83, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" title="Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" volume="79" year="1992">Kvist and Skog (1992)</bibRefCitation>
as the basis for the generic circumscription of 
<taxonomicName id="5E17DC16343A008E005CB566DE65DA96" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C4804F0A772BCA2EF12FDFEC4522D9E7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was a terrestrial (i.e., non-epiphytic) habit. In the generic delimitation of 
<taxonomicName id="016D082F74EFAE3A63866B932A08A62E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9F3FAE93CE316F1B1388DB5D6320A167" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="03D28B3B22E5B8A741EED7B532A86041" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" author="Kvist, L" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 83" refId="B4" refString="Kvist, L, Skog, LE, 1992. Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 79 (79): 1 - 83, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" title="Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" volume="79" year="1992">Kvist and Skog 1992</bibRefCitation>
), the habit is described as herbs, subshrubs, shrubs, or rarely scandent shrubs. The terrestrial habit was considered a character by 
<bibRefCitation id="D7B74B3979DE24448D65CDD3050F4289" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" author="Kvist, L" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="1 - 83" refId="B4" refString="Kvist, L, Skog, LE, 1992. Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 79 (79): 1 - 83, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" title="Revision of Kohleria (Gesneriaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.0081024X.79" volume="79" year="1992">Kvist and Skog (1992)</bibRefCitation>
to differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="A32397E51FA795FDCD338F93BCB8491C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="461863D20A5756DFE283B07A51952B81" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from closely related genera that are epiphytes or lianas. Phylogenetic studies by 
<bibRefCitation id="7C0981C7A45937F47643B17A85B1AE1C" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" author="Roalson, EH" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="389 - 410" refId="B6" refString="Roalson, EH, Boggan, JK, Skog, LE, Zimmer, EA, 2005b. Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets. Taxon 54 (2): 389 - 410, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" title="Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" volume="54" year="2005 b">Roalson et al. (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
showed that 
<taxonomicName id="71BB50F88D387DFD291993C81D56C288" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3183B13A206C36684FF1CBE580932435" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was paraphyletic with the exclusion of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="8BB68EC515CE97AC44D2A7EC4F512F1D" authority="Decne. ex Planch." authorityName="Decne. ex Planch." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Capanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capanea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4C72C1EC45533B3089011FE1BBA8309E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Capanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, a group of epiphytic subshrubs from the Andes. Thus, many of the features that differentiated &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="61AA907AD84C1B9EF9096E6BA0EAFCD5" authority="Decne. ex Planch." authorityName="Decne. ex Planch." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Capanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capanea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1B1CEC173BB452DA1B851E8B7506DE40" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Capanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; from 
<taxonomicName id="97C4E4F6EC87BEC54830E5CB94FC562B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A31499D151A84172805CFEA1699F2236" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as an epiphytic habit and four-valved capsules, are autapomorphic. The transfer of two species from &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="8D50ABE453242DC6E1B4BE91A02D1991" authority="Decne. ex Planch." authorityName="Decne. ex Planch." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Capanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capanea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D3111A274A442EE3C1409923BD00106A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Capanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; to 
<taxonomicName id="AEFA1E27A20A34CCD8AAB64E02CAC913" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A5AFEB2862F1219FB9D89DE6B046068A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is well-supported, and combinations were made by 
<bibRefCitation id="7688C4C00C9AD119977CC0E797720DB6" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" author="Roalson, EH" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="389 - 410" refId="B6" refString="Roalson, EH, Boggan, JK, Skog, LE, Zimmer, EA, 2005b. Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets. Taxon 54 (2): 389 - 410, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" title="Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" volume="54" year="2005 b">Roalson et al. (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="E0ABC03D00BFDEE750890C28EC3160EC" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" author="Roalson, EH" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" pagination="389 - 410" refId="B6" refString="Roalson, EH, Boggan, JK, Skog, LE, Zimmer, EA, 2005b. Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets. Taxon 54 (2): 389 - 410, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" title="Untangling Gloxinieae (Gesneriaceae). I. Phylogenetic patterns and generic boundaries inferred from nuclear, chloroplast, and morphological cladistic datasets." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/25065368" volume="54" year="2005 b">Roalson et al. (2005b)</bibRefCitation>
did not make a combination for 
<taxonomicName id="B418E37305B778BD24848236D36C2988" authorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Jost" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="J. L. Clark &amp; Jost" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria andina" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis id="0453EEF0F642D6D5F2A865A39A08862E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because it was considered a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="52799529754F34517ADAD0AD1A470A87" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria affinis" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="8144F549C4490979184209C2BD4C1448" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Examination of material in the field and in herbaria allowed us to recognize 
<taxonomicName id="5C1DF6A56085F077AB140AEFBE14E643" genus="K." lsidName="K. affinis" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="84629A0DC260091C1BE416DCA6BFAD89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">K. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="88FD0A69E228C0F134560672EB0FEF86" genus="K." lsidName="K. andina" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis id="3EC5F3D48D1138C58A8EB0FF719CCA0B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">K. andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as different species. Outlined here are characters to differentiate 
<taxonomicName id="5C13F58DD8326B94C241DEAE67129909" genus="K." lsidName="K. andina" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="andina">
<emphasis id="471A919CAD8CE5D61E0A3761E4B72535" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">K. andina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="57A9F2AF8D672E411464ECA6F35B8109" genus="K." lsidName="K. affinis" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="affinis">
<emphasis id="1DB0E277790F70C730193CA6A5FC7818" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">K. affinis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Table 
<tableCitation id="2191BA3049445AE3AEAB6C2E56F468C4" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological differences and general distribution of Kohleria affinis and K. andina." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/6773835BB260881B85C5B2D1963ECC66" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" tableUuid="6773835BB260881B85C5B2D1963ECC66">1</tableCitation>
for a summary of the characters that are discussed below).
</paragraph>
