</table>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BBBAF4FEF5FCB6A1A5EC2E7604FEEAB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">
Another feature that defines the clade previously recognized as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="3DB37BC4653418140C48372DC5F591B1" authority="Decne. ex Planch." authorityName="Decne. ex Planch." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Capanea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Capanea" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C917E264211004C424C9CD59A07DBF78" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Capanea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; is the presence of resupinate flowers via a twisted pedicel. The androecium and gynoecium are located in the lower region of the corolla tube (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="788CC7D8248BD15FB2AE56D8A777735E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Kohleria affinis (Fritsch) Roalson &amp; Boggan A lateral view of flower B female phase of mature flower C male phase of mature flower D habit (A Clark et al. 7698 B Clark s. n. C Clark et al. 12979 D Clark et al. 15845). Photos by J. L. Clark." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.179.65990.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/564817" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">1B, C</figureCitation>
and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CE4446B98F8FE73501D572A252A8F265" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Kohleria andina (Fritsch) J. L. Clark &amp; Jost A lateral view of flower B female phase of mature flower C male phase of mature flower D habit (A-D Clark et al. 7750). Photos by J. L. Clark." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.179.65990.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/564818" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">2B, C</figureCitation>
). In contrast, all other 
<taxonomicName id="EAC9BE3E03A7AA8281AE7300F53DB060" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Gesneriaceae" genus="Kohleria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Kohleria" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6E047759079FB37F0434F725E629F4CE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="99">Kohleria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and closely related genera have the androecium and gynoecium in the upper region of the corolla tube.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B87A7A989A14CCBFAF3B0AB994DD885B" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.179.65990.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/564817" pageId="0" pageNumber="99" start="Figure 1" startId="F1">
